  "sourceCode": "Employer Portal",
  "title": "Commerce Sales manager",
  "description": "<p><strong>Job Summary</strong></p><p>Report directly to the General Manager and drive business growth by developing new customer relationships and maintaining long-term partnerships. Lead customer engagement, manage payment collections, analyze sales data, and collaborate with internal teams to ensure optimal stock availability and market responsiveness.</p><p><strong>Responsibilities</strong></p><ul><li>Respond promptly and effectively to customer enquiries to secure new and potential business opportunities</li><li>Build and sustain long-term relationships with existing and new customers to enhance customer loyalty and retention</li><li>Manage and oversee customer payment collection processes to ensure timely and accurate transactions</li><li>Generate and analyze sales data to produce insightful reports for the General Manager, supporting informed decision-making</li></ul><p><strong>Preferred competencies and qualifications</strong></p><ul><li>Minimum ‘O’ Level/Diploma with relevant experience in sales or related fields</li><li>Experience in Wholesale, enhancing industry-specific knowledge and customer engagement</li><li>Proficiency in Mandarin and dialects to effectively communicate with diverse customer groups</li><li>Demonstrated independence, resourcefulness, and dynamism, with the ability to thrive as a collaborative team player in a fast-paced environment</li><li>Highly motivated and hardworking attitude to drive business objectives and personal performance</li></ul>",
